{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-template-js","path":"/linux/sha1-with-hmac-using-openssl.html","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Taking the message you want to authenticate and combining it with a secret key creates a \"message authentication code\" (MAC). HMAC stands for \"Hash-based Message Authentication Code\".</p>\n<p>Here's is how you calculate a hash using openssl cli:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">openssl dgst <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-sha1</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-mac</span> HMAC <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-macopt</span> hexkey:<span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">$(</span><span class=\"token builtin class-name\">echo</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-n</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"&lt;secret key string>\"</span> <span class=\"token operator\">|</span> od <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-A</span> n <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-t</span> x1 <span class=\"token operator\">|</span> <span class=\"token function\">sed</span> <span class=\"token string\">'s/ *//g'</span><span class=\"token variable\">)</span></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>file path<span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<ol>\n<li>Echo the secret key to standard output without a trailing newline character (<code class=\"language-text\">-n</code>).</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">od</code> stands for \"octal dump\".</li>\n</ol>\n<ul>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">-A n</code> - don't print the address of the input data</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">-t x1</code> - output the input data as a series of hexadecimal bytes</li>\n</ul>\n<ol start=\"3\">\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">'s/ *//g'</code> - removes any spaces between the hexadecimal bytes output</li>\n</ol>","excerpt":"Taking the message you want to authenticate and combining it with a secret key creates a \"message authentication code\" (MAC). HMAC stands…","tableOfContents":"","frontmatter":{"date":"May 26, 2022","published":"May 26, 2022","lastModified":"May 26, 2022","title":"SHA1 with HMAC using OpenSSL","subtitle":null,"section":null,"draft":null,"developing":null,"buttonText":null,"buttonLink":null,"secondButtonText":null,"secondButtonLink":null,"featuredImage":null}}},"pageContext":{"showLikes":true,"absolutePath":"/home/runner/work/mikolasan.github.io/mikolasan.github.io/src/markdown/linux/sha1-with-hmac-using-openssl.md","url":"/linux/sha1-with-hmac-using-openssl","next":{"excerpt":"If you experience lagging in some repositories when using the oh-my-zsh shell, then try to hide certain information in the prompt: The…","fileAbsolutePath":"/home/runner/work/mikolasan.github.io/mikolasan.github.io/src/markdown/linux/slow-zsh-in-git-repo.md","frontmatter":{"title":"Slow zsh in Git repo","date":"2022-06-03T00:00:00.000Z","topic":null,"article":null},"id":"4203de10-06ad-5bfb-ad8f-739f9cf84476"},"previous":{"excerpt":"System logs can be very useful for troubleshooting issues that occur on the system. So you might want to store logs persistently across…","fileAbsolutePath":"/home/runner/work/mikolasan.github.io/mikolasan.github.io/src/markdown/linux/persistent-logs-in-ubuntu.md","frontmatter":{"title":"Ubuntu persistent logs","date":"2022-05-24T00:00:00.000Z","topic":null,"article":null},"id":"89e14f35-1324-5bf6-9d8c-7aa848425e84"},"recentArticles":[{"excerpt":"How to fix invalid magic cookie You need a proper content in .Xautority because Xorg started by another user (it probably could be fixed by…","fileAbsolutePath":"/home/runner/work/mikolasan.github.io/mikolasan.github.io/src/markdown/linux/mit-magic-cookie